<ol>
<li>Select <strong>Syslog</strong>.
     <%= image_tag("../common/images/syslog_bosh.png") %>
</li>
<li>(Optional) Select <strong>Yes</strong> to send BOSH Director system logs to a remote server.</li>
<li>Enter the IP address or DNS name for the remote server in the <strong>Address</strong> field.
</li>
<li>Enter the port number that the remote server listens on in the <strong>Port</strong> field.</li>
<li>Select <strong>TCP</strong> or <strong>UDP</strong> from the <strong>Transport Protocol</strong> dropdown. This selection determines which transport protocol is used to send the logs to the remote server.</li>
<li>(Optional) Select the <strong>Enable TLS</strong> checkbox to send encrypted logs to remote server via TLS. After you select the checkbox, perform the following steps:<br/>
	<ul>
	  <li>Enter either the name or SHA1 fingerprint of the remote peer in the <strong>Permitted Peer</strong> field.</li>
	  <li>Enter the SSL certificate for the remote server in the <strong>SSL Certificate</strong> field.</li>
	</ul>
  <p class="note"><strong>Note</strong>: Pivotal strongly recommends that you enable TLS encryption when you are forwarding logs. Logs can contain sensitive information, such as cloud provider credentials.</p>
</li>
<li>(Optional) Enter an integer in the <strong>Queue Size</strong> field. This value specifies the number of log messages held in the buffer. The default value is 100,000.</li>
<li>Click <strong>Save</strong>.</li>
</ol>
